Privacy Policy

Last updated: 23.03.2026

This Privacy Policy explains how the Baby Sleep app (“the App”) handles user data.

1. Information We Collect

The App does not collect personal information and does not transmit data to external servers.

All sleep tracking data entered by the user is stored locally on the user’s device.

Examples of stored data may include:
	•	Sleep start time
	•	Sleep end time
	•	Sleep duration
	•	Basic usage information required for app functionality

This data is stored only on the user’s device and is not accessible to the developer.

⸻

2. Data Storage

All data recorded in the App is stored locally on the device using secure local storage.

The developer does not have access to this data.

If the app is deleted, the stored data may also be removed from the device.

⸻

3. Data Sharing

The App does not share data with third parties.

The App does not use:
	•	external analytics services
	•	advertising networks
	•	tracking technologies

Users may optionally export their data manually (if the export feature is used).

⸻

4. Children’s Privacy

The App is designed for parents and caregivers to track sleep patterns.

The App does not knowingly collect personal information about children.

⸻

5. Medical Disclaimer

The App provides informational insights based on recorded sleep data.

It is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.

Users should consult qualified healthcare professionals for medical concerns.

⸻

6. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated in the future to reflect improvements to the App.

